BT 1 0 0 1 7.875 21.8555 Tm 7.875 TL /F1 5.25 Tf 0 0 0 rg (MAC vs. AC - DAC: Discretionary access control - Ownership \(user, group, other\) + permissions \(rwx\) - Users have ability \(discretion\) to change permissions - User can do chmod +rwx on his home) Tj T* (directory, no way to stop that - Problem: Execute anything he wants in his home dir! - MAC: Mandatory access control - Policy that is administratively set and fixed - Even if DAC is changed on home dir,) Tj T* (nothing happens, as if there is a policy that prevents users and processes from accessing it) Tj T* ET
